pageContext.description: Dimensions: EL 43mm; maxEW 27.2mm; maxEB 20.2; maxTsep 10mm; wt 70.4 gms,Typology: butt prob. fairly square originally, top uncertain; 'U' shaped sep. section,Manufacture: rippling in sep. probably cast mouldings, at least in part - otherwide hammer marks; distortion of mould valves evident for one side, rev. in line; blow hole in break,Condition: main break anc. - of one fg. broken also, butt corner uncertain,Attached Material: little orange staining.
pageContext.surface: Dull olive green patina surviving on much of one face and little on sides; rest deteriorated to rough pale green surface
pageContext.collection: Trill, Mr. E. - private no. 3,Pine Lodge, Fairley Park, Ringwood, Hants
